text.tspan: Community database of music features extracted from audio
Open data computed by open algorithms (Essentia Music Extractor)
Built on submissions from the community
Statistical information about timbre, rhythm, tonality, loudness, etc.
Goal: Predict genre and subgenre of unknown music recordings
Four different genre annotation sources (and taxonomies)
A very large dataset (~2 million recordings in total)
Per recording, all labels (genres and subgenres)
Random baseline: following the distribution of labels
Popularity baseline: always predicts the most popular genre
Maximum 5 submissions for each task per team (5x2x4 = 40 runs)
TODO screenshots from discogs, allmusic, lastfm?
Subgenre recognition task is more difficult than genre
High recall, but poor precision for many systems
No significant improvement from combining genre sources
